{
  "stem": "942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We grew our food, vegetables and other things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And flour-- you know, we were able to buy flour to bake bread and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So there was rationing, but we really didn't suffer any hunger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember in 1941, my maternal grandmother and my uncles were taken away from Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the way we found this out-- because their cattle herd was being brought to their grazing fields in Hungary because that land belonged to them, but the border happened to come right across the middle of this field.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the herdsman used to bring the herd of cattle over to the Hungarian side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had some relatives living in this town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandmother used to send with the herdsmen once every now and then cheeses and butter and so on, and they used to hand it over to these relatives of ours.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one day in 1941, they told these relatives, the herdsmen, that our-- that my grandmother and uncle were taken away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember receiving-- we received a card from Lublin that they arrived there, and they are working.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But these were cards, I know now, that the Germans had prearranged and to sort of quiet everybody's fears.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we realized that they were taken to Lublin, and we never heard from them ever again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's my maternal grandmother, uncles, three aunts, and many, many cousins.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would say a total of about 40, extended family of about 40 people from my mother's side, you know, they just disappeared.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There wasn't a single survivor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So 19-- by 1942, the next thing that the Hungarians did-- they were taking some Jewish people out of Hungary, shipping them out to Poland to occupy Poland, a place called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
